						<summary>

						<p>This is built in at the beginning. It is dated in the 9th year of a king whose name is lost. It might probably be Uttama-Chōḷa. It seems to record the gift of a quarter (<hi rend="italic">vēli</hi>) of land free of taxes as <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> to the temple of Kūṟṟakkuḍi-Paramēśvara by the <hi rend="italic">Ūrār</hi> of Peruṅkūṟṟakkuḍi on an order received from Vīraśōḻa-Iḷaṅgō [vēḷār] (Koḍumbāḷūr chief) to provide for the daily offerings to the deity. Mention is made in the body of the record, of Madhurāntakadēva.</p>						

						</summary>
